{{Infobox language |name=Karingani |nativename= |states=[[Iran]] |region= |speakers={{sigfig|17600|2}} |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Indo-European |fam2=[[Indo-Iranian languages|Indo-Iranian]] |fam3=[[Iranian languages|Iranian]] |fam4=[[Western Iranian languages|Western]] |fam5=[[Northwestern Iranian languages|Northwestern II]] |fam6=Tatic |fam7=[[Tati language (Iran)|Tati/Azari]] |iso3=kgn |glotto=kari1303 |glottorefname=Karingani }} '''Karingani''' is a [[Northwestern Iranian languages|Northwestern Iranian language]] closely related to [[Talysh language|Talysh]] and the [[Harzandi dialect]]. It is spoken in [[East Azerbaijan Province]], in the Dizmar district, [[Karangan, East Azerbaijan|Keringan]] village, and Hasanu district, northeast of [[Tabriz]].{{sfn|Frawley|2003|p=310}}
