'''Indian Nepali''', '''Indian Nepalese''' or '''Indo Nepalese''' are [[Nepali people|Nepalese (Nepali people)]] who have total or partial Indian heritage. The migrants are both Madhesis having origins from Bihar, UP & other states and Pahadis from Assam , Darjeeling ,etc. There are a large number of Indian immigrants in Nepal, consisting of recent migrants from [[India]] to [[Nepal]]. There are currently estimated over 4 million Indian origin immigrants living in Nepal.<ref name=TheHindu/>

