{{Infobox language |name=Persian Sign Language |nativename= |states=[[Iran]] |speakers=?<!--no speaker numbers in the Ethnologue18--> |familycolor=sign |family=''unknown'' |iso3=psc |glotto=pers1244 |glottorefname=Persian Sign Language }}
'''Persian Sign Language''' is the sign language used by [[Deaf]] and [[hard-of-hearing]] people in [[Iran]]. It is a true sign language, unlike the [[Jabbar Baghtcheban|Baghcheban]] phonetic hand alphabet, which is a form of [[cued speech]].
