'''Samoan Plantation Pidgin''' is an [[English language|English]]-based [[pidgin language]] that was spoken by [[plantation]] workers in [[Samoa]]. It is closely related to [[Tok Pisin]], due to the large number of [[New Guinea]]n laborers in Samoa.

