{{Infobox WorldScouting |image=Scouting for Food.png |f-date=1985 }}
'''Scouting for Food''' is an ongoing annual program of the [[Boy Scouts of America]], begun in 1985 by the [[Greater Saint Louis Area Council]]<ref>[http://www.stlbsa.org/programs/sff/Pages/Scouting-for-Food.aspx STLBSA]</ref>. The program involves collecting for local food banks. It is organized at the local level throughout the country.<ref>[http://www.northjersey.com/community/announcements/121756903_Pack_45_collects_food_for_St__Mary_s_Church_pantry.html Pack 45 collects food for St. Mary's Church pantry]</ref>
Scouting for Food is a project rooted in the very foundation of the Scouting movement and its dedication to implement the [[Scout Slogan]] and do a good turn daily.<ref>[http://www.longhorncouncil.org/uploads/df/df051deb-3750-4bdd-bf7d-b1839e60cf13.pdf SFF Background]</ref>
==Background== Each year, local Cub and Boy Scouts leave plastic bags for their neighbors soliciting canned food items. One week later, the Scouts return to pick up and deliver the bags of food to a local [[food bank]]. The donations will usually be delivered directly to the local food bank that day. The time of Collection is usually the Saturday before Thanksgiving.
==References== {{reflist}}
==External links== * [http://www.boyscouttrail.com/scouting-for-food.asp Scouting for Food, How to] * Buckner, Simon C. "Scouting for Food." Personal interview. 18 Nov. 2017.
